==English==

===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[prorogare]]'' "to publicly ask".

===Verb===
'''prorogue''' ([[prorogues]], [[prorogued]], [[proroguing]])

# {{transitive}} To [[suspend]] a [[parliamentary]] [[session]] or to [[discontinue]] the [[meeting]]s of a parliament without formally ending the session.

===Derived terms===
*[[prorogation]]